		<p> In order to get to the ship for the tour to the Franklands Icelands, we had to drive south for 45 minutes, as the boat does not go from Cairns, but on a small hidden investor between the field and jungle. The trip to the islands only went a cozy 25 min on a river through the rainforest. We both hoped to see a crocodile. Unfortunately we were not lucky. As soon as the boat stretched out the nose on the open sea, the swell started. It's good that firstly we had traveled tablets and secondly there were only another 25 minutes up to the island. I would not have tolerated much longer today. </p>
		<p> When we arrived on the island, we made it comfortable with 16 other day guests on some parking benches. Since this is a nature conservation park, these benches are the only one that people changed here on the island. </p>
